to name his accomplishment. That would be Alex Olmedo. . . . Olmedo, 58, beat 
Rod Laver to win the Wimbledon tennis title in 1959. He's still on top of his 
game, making the finals last week at the U.S. Tennis Assn.'s 55-and-over 
national singles hard-court championships (C10). 
