<HEADLINE>
<P>
GILMORE CONTINUES TO BE AN INFLUENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thank you for Lynell George's article on Mikal Gilmore ("A Legacy Survived," 
July 6). 
</P>
<P>
 I have been an admirer of Gilmore since his days as a rock critic for the 
(now-defunct) Los Angeles Herald Examiner. Reading his reviews of artists 
ranging from Prince to Fleetwood Mac to Johnny Cash to the Sex Pistols made me 
seek out music I otherwise may not have discovered. 
</P>
<P>
 That Gilmore overcame a background of family violence and pain is truly an 
inspiration to me. 
</P>
<P>
 KEN GRAHAM 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
