<HEADLINE>
<P>
ONE KOREAN AMERICAN INSPIRES ANOTHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As a young Korean American architecture student, I am proud to know the recent 
addition to the Los Angeles Convention Center was designed by a Korean 
American. "One Man's Vision" (June 26) about Ki Suh Park, was refreshing. 
</P>
<P>
 I have for some time been lost and confused and could not really grasp why I 
am not as motivated as before. I have let down my teachers who went out of 
their way to help me and I let myself down. 
</P>
<P>
 But the ordeals and obstacles Park overcame were obviously far more difficult. 
That is why I'm writing to thank you for a great article. It is wonderful to 
find Koreans are being recognized in a profession such as architecture, and not 
just as grocery merchants.  
</P>
<P>
 I don't mean to degrade merchants, but am only trying to express my happiness 
that we are recognized. I think there are many things young Korean Americans 
can contribute to the community. 
</P>
<P>
 KYUNG KIM 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
