PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NFL; FLOYD ENDS HOLDOUT, SIGNS WITH 
49ERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullback William Floyd, the second of the San Francisco 49ers' two first-round 
picks, signed a four-year contract worth $2.78 million. Floyd played at Florida 
State. 
</P>
<P>
 The Arizona Cardinals lost two safeties to injury in practice Thursday 
morning, so coach and general manager Buddy Ryan quickly signed another of his 
former players, Andre Waters, an 11-year veteran. 
</P>
