ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; LAW ENFORCEMENT INFORMATION OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Need to register your bicycle? Want to become a retired senior volunteer for a 
law enforcement agency? 
</P>
<P>
 Then the place to go Saturday is the Ortega Business Center from 11 a.m. to 3 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Representatives from the Orange County Sheriff's Department, the Fire 
Department, the California Highway Patrol and the Border Patrol will be on hand 
to describe their law enforcement strategies and how members of the public can 
participate in local anti-crime programs. 
</P>
<P>
 As part of National Day Out, which is observed by law enforcement agencies 
across the country to heighten awareness of crime and drug prevention, they 
also will provide free fingerprinting of children and free bicycle 
registration. 
</P>
<P>
 Information will be available too on volunteer opportunities for retired 
seniors. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is open to residents of San Juan Capistrano, San Clemente and Dana 
Point. 
</P>
<P>
 The law enforcement agencies are also asking that people leave on their porch 
lights the evening of Aug. 2 as a signal to criminals that they support fire 
and crime prevention and drug education. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ortega Business Center is at Ortega Highway and Rancho Viejo Road. LYNN 
FRANEY 
</P>
