<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SCHOOL BUS FEES LOWERED FOR SOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFFREY BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback Valley Unified School District trustees made it cheaper Wednesday 
for parents with two or more children riding the bus to school. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustees voted unanimously to approve the new bus fee schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 The change will not affect families with one child who rides the bus, but 
families with two or more children will save from $230 to $412.50 per year in 
comparison to the old fees. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the old fee schedule, a family with two children who rode the bus would 
pay $730. 
</P>
<P>
 Now, they will pay $500, which is the most any family will be charged. 
</P>
<P>
 A family with three or more children riding the bus was charged $912.50 under 
the previous fee schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 Families with one child riding the bus still will be charged $365 a year under 
the adopted change. 
</P>
<P>
 The charge for a second child is $135, while a third child or more are free. 
</P>
<P>
 The district was able to offer the bus-fee reductions after saving money by 
contracting with a new transportation company. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustee Frank L. Ury said he wanted parents with children who ride the bus to 
receive a bigger break because of the money the district saved by switching bus 
companies. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think it is a great half-step," Ury said, adding that about 200 families 
would benefit. 
</P>
<P>
 But other trustees said they wanted to take a more conservative approach in 
the event the district's budget is hard hit later by cuts. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustee Marcia Birch said she hoped the new fees would remain in place at 
least three years. JEFFREY BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
