 Two Firms Invest in Showscan Corp.: Culver City-based Showscan said two firms 
bought more than 500,000 of its newly issued common shares, amounting to 9.8% 
of its outstanding common stock after the effect of the sales. The company, a 
leader in the production of entertainment motion-simulation theater 
attractions, said Fidelity Investments bought 357,040 shares at $7.75 each, or 
