<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY & TELECOMMUNICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bidding for Paging Licenses Still Rising: Defying most predictions, the 
government's first auction for public airwaves completed its fourth day, with 
bidders raising the ante to nearly $610 million.At least 10 companies are still 
in the running to win 10 nationwide licenses to offer an array of advanced 
wireless communications services, including two-way paging and messaging, on a 
nationwide basis. Anxious to bring the hammer down, the Federal Communications 
Commission, which is holding the auction, has quickened the pace of the 
bidding. Bids for the most coveted licenses shot up to a range of $77 million 
to $80 million. 
</P>
