<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; YOUTH CONNECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Tricia Michels, junior; Fountain Valley High 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Getting the word out to potential volunteers may be a bit easier for the 
Volunteer Center of Greater Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Its Youth Connection Program recently received a $25,000 grant from the 
Weingart Foundation for a three-year program designed to increase volunteer 
service. 
</P>
<P>
 The program plans to increase the number of nonprofit agencies offering youth 
volunteer opportunities, to develop a working network of information sharing 
and referral service and to increase training and consultation between the 
Volunteer Center and high schools. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers from 10 Orange County high schools this month participated in a 
beach cleanup sponsored by the Youth Connection Program at Crystal Cove Beach 
in Laguna. The next summer volunteer project will be Aug. 10. For information, 
call Cynthia Lanois at the Youth Connection Program, (714) 953-5757. Tricia 
Michels, junior; Fountain Valley High 
</P>
