<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; LIFE AND TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Time is precious, but during a lifetime the average American spends a lot of 
it doing less than precious things.Statisticians have estimated that: 
</P>
<P>
 * The average American spends eight months opening junk mail. 
</P>
<P>
 * Six years consuming food and drink and five years waiting in line. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bathroom basics take seven years, while housework cleans up another four. 
</P>
<P>
 * Most drivers spend a total of six months waiting for red lights to change. 
</P>
</TEXT>
