<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; H.O.R.D.E. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By OC Live! 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A daylong rock festival Saturday brings to Irvine the Allman Brothers Band, 
Blues Traveler, Big Head Todd and the Monsters and Sheryl Crow as part of the 
32-city H.O.R.D.E. (for Horizons of Rock Developing Everywhere) tour.A 
midway-style concourse will include attractions such as a virtual-reality "LSD 
flight simulator," Jimi Hendrix memorabilia and a mechanical bucking bull ride. 
At the Irvine Meadows Amphitheatre beginning at 12:30 p.m. Tickets are $22.50 
and $30. Call (714) 855-6111 or (714) 740-2000 (TicketMaster). 
</P>
