<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: AUTOMOBILES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John O'Dell, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hyundai Recall: Owners of almost 250,000 1988 and 1989 Hyundai Excels will be 
getting letters from the company next month asking them to bring their cars to 
an authorized dealer to repair a potentially faulty heater valve. 
</P>
<P>
 Hyundai Motor America, based in Fountain Valley, imports and distributes the 
Korean-made cars in the United States. The company said it has determined that 
the valves could malfunction and cause engine coolant to leak into the 
passenger compartment. 
</P>
<P>
 Repairs will be made at no charge to the car owners. 
</P>
