<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: INTERBIKE NAMES FORMER TRADE SHOW EXHIBITORS IN 
ANTITRUST SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Interbike, which produces bicycle industry trade shows, has sued a number of 
former exhibitors alleging antitrust violations in connection with the creation 
a new, competing expo. 
</P>
<P>
 Interbike, based in Newport Beach, hosts trade shows in Anaheim and 
Philadelphia.The company alleges that Schwinn Cycling & Fitness Inc., Yakima 
Products Inc. and several other manufacturers violated antitrust laws last year 
when they organized the competing Bicycle Industry Organization trade show and 
allegedly pressured other manufacturers to skip Interbike's annual events. 
</P>
<P>
 The lawsuit, filed in federal court in Los Angeles, alleges that the 
manufacturers created their own trade organization in a bid to ruin Interbike. 
A Bicycle Industry Organization spokesman said Thursday that the group has not 
seen a copy of the suit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
