STADIUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Conejo Valley school board awarded a $1.4-million contract to Carroll 
Construction Co. this week to build an athletic stadium at Westlake High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 The Santa Barbara-based company presented the lowest of three bids for the 
project, which is expected to be completed by May of next year. 
</P>
<P>
 But even the lowest bid was more than the school district had planned to pay 
for the new 3,646-seat concrete stadium, which is being financed primarily 
through community donations. 
</P>
<P>
 "The bids were higher than we anticipated they would be," board member Dorothy 
Beaubien said Thursday. "There will be some shortfall, but it will be made up. 
It is not a major problem." 
</P>
<P>
 About $1.2-million has been raised for the project, leaving a shortfall of 
about $250,000 to $300,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Board member Mildred Lynch said the money will be made up through funds the 
district receives from city redevelopment taxes. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction of the stadium will start at the end of August. TRACY WILSON 
