By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Firefighters on Thursday doused a fire of unknown origin that destroyed a 
young couple's Camarillo garage and charred a white car parked in front of it. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris and Tia Bush reported the fire in their garage at 3188 Belair Court at 
7:06 a.m. after being alerted by neighbors, who spotted smoke pouring out of 
the structure, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Firefighters from three engine companies extinguished the blaze about 30 
minutes later, after freeing a dog from the back yard, said county fire 
dispatcher Vicki Sosa. No one was injured. 
</P>
